name: Fred Warmsley
description: '''Fred Welton Warmsley III''' (born September 22, 1987) is an American [[record producer]] and [[sound artist]] from [[Sacramento, California]]. Initially known for his work with the East Coast hip hop collective [[Pro Era]], he has since produced in several genres including [[breakcore]], [[Ambient music|ambient]] and [[noise music]]. He has released eight extended plays and two albums since 2013, including his critically acclaimed debut ''[[Alternate/Endings]]'' (2013) and its follow-up, ''[[Successor (Dedekind Cut album)|$uccessor]]'' (2016).{{unreliable source inline|date=December 2023}}
